---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const EFFECTIVE_DATE = "February 14, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — AOHSTD"
  description="Terms that govern your access to and use of AOHSTD services."
  active="terms"
>
  <header class="policy-header">
    <span class="badge">Effective Date: {EFFECTIVE_DATE}</span>
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p>
      These Terms of Use (“Terms”) govern your access to and use of AOHSTD mobile
      applications and websites (collectively, the “Services”). By accessing or
      using the Services, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="section" id="acceptance">
    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the Services. You agree
        to comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and platform rules
        (including Google Play and Apple App Store policies).
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="eligibility">
    <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        You must be legally capable of entering into these Terms. If you are
        using the Services on behalf of an organization, you represent that
        you have authority to bind that organization to these Terms.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="license">
    <h2>3. Use of the Services</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Subject to these Terms, AOHSTD grants you a limited, non-exclusive,
        non-transferable, revocable license to access and use the Services for
        personal, non-commercial purposes, unless explicitly stated otherwise.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Do not misuse the Services or interfere with normal operation.</li>
        <li>Do not attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or bypass security measures.</li>
        <li>Do not use the Services to violate laws or third-party rights.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="billing">
    <h2>4. Subscriptions and Billing</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Some features may require a paid subscription or in-app purchase.
        Billing is processed by the platform provider (e.g., Google Play or Apple App Store).
        Subscription details (price, billing cycle, renewal, cancellation, refunds)
        are presented at the time of purchase and are governed by the platform provider’s terms.
      </p>
      <p>
        Subscriptions may automatically renew unless cancelled in accordance with
        the platform provider’s rules.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="content">
    <h2>5. User Content</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Some Services may allow you to submit content (e.g., images, text, files) (“User Content”).
        You retain ownership of your User Content. However, you grant AOHSTD a limited license
        to host, process, and transmit User Content solely for the purpose of operating the Services
        and providing the requested functionality (for example, generating a scan result).
      </p>
      <p>
        You represent and warrant that you have all necessary rights to submit the User Content and that
        it does not infringe or violate any third-party rights or applicable laws.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="thirdparty">
    <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        The Services may rely on third-party services (for example, analytics, diagnostics,
        payment processing by platform providers, or infrastructure hosting). AOHSTD is not
        responsible for third-party services outside of its control, and your use of such services
        may be subject to their separate terms and policies.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="ip">
    <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        The Services (including software, design, text, graphics, and branding) are owned by AOHSTD
        or its licensors and are protected by intellectual property laws. These Terms do not grant you
        any rights to use AOHSTD trademarks, logos, or branding without prior written permission.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="disclaimer">
    <h2>8. Disclaimers</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        The Services are provided “as is” and “as available”, without warranties of any kind,
        whether express, implied, or statutory, to the maximum extent permitted by law.
      </p>
      <p>
        AOHSTD does not warrant that the Services will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure.
        Certain features may provide informational outputs or estimates that are not guaranteed to be accurate.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="liability">
    <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, AOHSTD will not be liable for any indirect, incidental,
        special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or revenues, whether incurred
        directly or indirectly, or any loss of data, use, goodwill, or other intangible losses, resulting from:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your access to or use of (or inability to access or use) the Services;</li>
        <li>Any conduct or content of any third party;</li>
        <li>Unauthorized access, use, or alteration of your transmissions or content.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="termination">
    <h2>10. Termination</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We may suspend or terminate access to the Services at any time if we reasonably believe you have
        violated these Terms, or if required to do so to comply with law or protect the Services.
      </p>
      <p>
        You may stop using the Services at any time. Sections that by their nature should survive termination
        (including intellectual property, disclaimers, and limitation of liability) will survive.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="changes">
    <h2>11. Changes to These Terms</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. The updated version will be indicated by the revised
        Effective Date above. Continued use of the Services after changes become effective constitutes acceptance
        of the updated Terms.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="law">
    <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by applicable laws. Where required, mandatory consumer protection laws in your
        jurisdiction may apply and prevail.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="contact">
    <h2>13. Contact</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Contact
        <a class="link" href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">support@aohstd.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
      <a href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">support@aohstd.com</a>
    </div>
    <small>© {new Date().getFullYear()} AOHSTD</small>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
